response.overview: Kattail: Strange Bird Flying is a fascinating year-in-the-life documentary of rising new folk singer/songwriter Kattail. The film features exclusive clips of Kattail's eclectic, soulful voice and songs from her 2013 debut album. In a series of refreshingly honest interviews and behind-the-scenes footage culled from her first two music videos "Change The Song" and "Cottage Grove", Kattail: Strange Bird Flying is an important, powerful and elegant reflection of a young and talented artist's life and dreams. An inspiration for anyone on a creative journey. Directed by Stewart St. John. Camera by Max Well, Dan Wong and Stewart St. John. Executive Producers Stewart St. John & Todd Fisher An SFN Media Group Production
response.title: Kattail: Strange Bird Flying
